Imagine you have someone you care about deeply. What are the things you want to do for them or like doing for them? Now imagine that person is yourself. Then you'll realize just how much self-worth you really have.

I've been thinking a lot about what self-care is. If you had to take care of a child, would you get them fast food and make them binge video games? Am I really caring for myself by giving into numbing mechanisms? 

More importantly, I think self-care is a perspective.
